The evidence with the title 'How dangerous is the U.S. current account deficit? | St. Louis Fed ' says As shown in the figure below, the U.S. current account deficit has been increasing  ... By the end of 2004 , foreigners owned more than $12.5 trillion of U.S. assets ,  ... Over half of the total amount of U.S. currency outstanding is circulating abroad .  ... The foreign holding of U.S. assets is in the form of Treasury bills and other debt  ... 
